{"word":"τριβώλετερ","slug":"τριβώλετερ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n104839\" key=\"tribw/leter\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">τρῑβώλετερ</orth>, obscure word found only in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0383.tlg001:38\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Alc.\">Alc.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">38</biblScope> </bibl>: cited by <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg1402.tlg001:11:3\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Heph.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">11.3</biblScope></bibl>, who attests its metrical form (--<pron extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"pron\">̆̆</pron>), and by <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4093.tlg001:1:262\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Choerob.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">in Theod.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.262</biblScope> </bibl> H., al., who says it is an <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Aeol.\">Aeol.</a></gram> </gramGrp> voc., proparox., and means <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">εἶδος ἀκάνθης</foreign>: the quantity is against Bergk's derivation from <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Τρῐβολολετηρ</foreign> 'caltrop-devourer'. [<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τριβωλ-</foreign> codd. <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Heph.</author></bibl>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τριβολ-, τρεβολ-,</foreign> and <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τριβαλ-</foreign> codd.<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Choerob.</author> </bibl>]</entryFree>"}]}